oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Military Bridge and Tennessee River distant view, circa 1863
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black-and-white photograph of the Tennessee River located in Chattanooga, Tennessee with Lookout Mountain in the background. Also depicted is the military bridge erected during the United States Civil War. Following the destruction of the Military Bridge, Chattanooga was without a bridge until the Walnut Street Bridge was constructed in 1891.
